The paper deals with fundamental graph parameters such as diameter, eccentricity, and extremal distance spanners, and presents algorithms for maintaining and approximating these parameters in static, dynamic, and fault-tolerant settings. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
